Date:- 12.03.2025

Practical No:- 07

Problem Specification:- Perform basic arithmetic operations using integers and display the results

Implementation:- 
class Exercise03{
	public static void main(String args[])
	{
	int num1=10;
	int num2=20;
	
	System.out.println("Addition= "+(num1+num2));
	System.out.println("Subtraction= "+(num1-num2));
	System.out.println("Multipication= "+(num1*num2));
	System.out.println("Division= "+(num1/num2));
	System.out.println("Mod= "+(num1%num2));
	}
}

Output:-
Addition: 30
Subtraction: -10
Multiplication: 200
Division: 0
Mod: 10

Conclusion:- Using arithmetic operators, we can efficiently perform mathematical calculations.
